column2: This file documents the filenames for ASIST Study 3, and inventories the files and quality control issues.
Jared Freeman and the ASU team
TA3 revises and publishes this document as a csv when new data are transferred to the ASIST data repository.
TA1 & TA2 performers should use this worksheet to assess the state of data in the ASIST repository and to interpret file names.
The master version of this document is here: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1PTPVqQ6JUC9IcgSB6dF9tTPIiYukVmkP237MBNyJDBo/edit#gid=1324771064
Data described below are available on GCS here: https://console.cloud.google.com/storage/browser/studies.aptima.com/study-3_2022
The study to which these files pertain is documented here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1GF7VsNF9R95IAaj6mVZUDV2mAX5ok1Bh6Tcm8zDpIkg/edit#heading=h.gjdgxs
The researchers' laboratory notebook (available only to TA3): https://docs.google.com/document/d/1KMxxbdkZbCTmJwkK9wfsDyyruU1MPrB1Evvl11AhXwg/edit#heading=h.v16ui0ddz6nv

Known issues in the testbed / task environment:
In at least one instance (Trial 608), a participant (Transporter) takes a victim to all three zones but no chime or points occur
In at least one instance (Trial 611), a participant (Transporter) picks up victim_id 18, but magically puts down victim_id 13.
In at least one instance (Team 205), a participant has difficulty picking up a victim.
In at least one instance in or before no-advisor trials, a critical victim would not wake up in the presence of all participants. This bug was fixed after no-advisor trials were completed.
In some cases prior to ASI-advisor trials, a json message reports that a destroyed marker is not of the type of that marker but is the type the player is holding.
In some cases, there is a discrepancy between messages in Dozzle logs and those in *TrialMessages*.metadata files (i.e., one includes messages that the other does not).
In some cases, a message from MQTT may not be valid json (e.g., it may be an empty string).
The Rutgers AC  published some “NaN” and “Infinity” Python values, which are technically malformed JSON. Strict json parsers may not have processed these well.

In some cases (e.g., Team 97 Trial 495, around 10:39), a victim (call it A) placed in the treatment area rewards points only to another victim (B), after which no points can be awarded to B. This is a function of the sequence in which a participant holding two victims picks up and places a victim on a particular block.
In some cases, the agent/asr/final messages (and consequently agent/dialog messages) have participant_id set to things like GREEN_ASIST1 instead of the PID: P000104

In no-advisor and human-advisor trials, in the metadata files only, the scale of teammate satisfication in Mission 1 and 2 reflection survey was reported on 12367, instead of 12345. On the ASI-advisor trials, the correct range is used: 12345. Users of this datum should use the correct Qualtrics output data. If it is needed to use the metadata files, then colrrect the value of these fields and dependent fields.
Background speech may influence ASR (automated speech recognition) in some teams or trials. No analysis has yet identified specific teams and trials that have this issue.

Teams run before 5/18/22 used a version of GOLD that produced missing or incorrect values. A subsequent version of TrialMessages*.metadata files may be available (see below in the future) to rectify this problem.

column2: Filenames are designed to be highly descriptive of contents. Each name consists of several components delimited by "_". Most components consist of a key and value delimited by "-" (e.g., Trial-T######). Where the value is "na" or "none", the data in the file span all possible values (e.g., Trial-na spans all trials by that team; Member-na indicates that data from all members of a team are in the file.)

[Missing] indicates that the named file is empty, typically because of a data capture failure on the client or server. These data cannot be recovered. [Terminated] indicates that a file contains an incomplete trial. All files named Terminated have a corresponding correct file (without that prefix) or an empty file (prefixed "Missing"). Terminated files are not present in the public dataset.

[HSRData,NotHSRData]_ Note: HSR designates Human Subjects Research data. Use is subject to the conditions in the Informed Consent document and decisions by your organization's Institutional Review Board for the protection of human subjects.

[TrialMessages, QCTrialMessages, QCAgentTrialMessages, Surveys-[#]-[Fulltext,Numeric], ZoomVideo, OBVideo, ZoomAudio, ZoomAudioTranscript, ClientAudio, Log, Observations-[#]-[type tbd], DockerLogs][-Part#]_ (Part# designates the first (Part1) and second (Part2) rounds of training for serveral participants who required two rounds of training to perform adequately) (QCAgentTrialMessages files report tests of the trialmessages files against predicates specified by agent developers. These files exist only for NoAdvisor and HumanAdvisor trials that were replayed after completion of Study-3 to correct the output of some analytic components (measurement agents)).
Member-[P###### (for pilot data (NotHSRData)),E###### (for human subjects research data (HSRData)), HumanAdvisor (for videos used to train a human advisor), na]_
